@page "/AboutUs"

<style>
    /* Partial-page background */
    .background {
        position: fixed;
        top: 0;
        left: 240px; /* Adjust this value to start the background image to the right of the sidebar */
        width: calc(100% - 240px); /* Adjust width to leave space for sidebar */
        height: 100%;
        background-image: url('/blur-background.ico');
        background-size: cover;
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
        background-position: center;
        z-index: -1; /* Place background behind the content */
    }

    .avenir {
        font-family: "Avenir", "Avenir Next", "Helvetica Neue", sans-serif;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: #C8102E; /* Red color */
    }

    .red-rectangle {
        background-color: #C8102E; /* Red background color */
        color: #FFFFFF; /* White text color */
        padding: 20px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        margin: 20px auto;
        width: 80%;
        max-width: 800px;
        display: block;
        clear: both;
    }

    .heading {
        font-weight: bold;
        font-size: 1.5em;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
        margin-top: 20px;
    }

    .content {
        font-size: 1.2em;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .container {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
    }

    .center-container {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 20px 0;
    }

    .heading {
        font-size: 2em;
        margin: 0;
    }

    .heading3 {
        font-weight: bold;
        font-size: 1.5em;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
        margin-top: 20px;
    }
</style>

<div class="background"></div> <!-- Partial-page background image -->

<div class="container">
    <div class="center-container">
        <h1 class="heading">About Us</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="red-rectangle">
        <h2 class="heading">Who We Are</h2>
        <p class="content">
            The YMCA South Africa is a dynamic and inclusive organization committed to strengthening communities.
            With a rich history dating back to 1872, it has been a haven for youth development, social justice, and holistic growth.
            The YMCA South Africa serves as a platform for individuals of all ages, backgrounds, and abilities to come together,
            foster connections, and create positive change.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="red-rectangle">
        <h2 class="heading">About YMCA South Africa</h2>

        <h3 class="heading3">Our Mission</h3>
        <p class="content">
            Empowering young people for life, leadership, and service.
        </p>
        <h3 class="heading3">Our Vision</h3>
        <p class="content">
            Young people and communities are empowered to build a just, sustainable, equitable, and inclusive world.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="red-rectangle">
        <h2 class="heading">Our History</h2>
        <p class="content">
            YMCA South Africa was established in 1942. It has grown through the years to become one of the strongest
            movements on the continent. It has 14 active local associations spread across the country.
            It currently enjoys full membership status with the Africa Alliance of YMCAs.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

